n. One nocturnal and one diurnal, the two ceremonials represented different scenarios, testifying to the capacity of church builders and willingness of Late Antique bishops to stage the ritual experience in order to offer God to the senses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aArchitecturexItalyxRavenna. 0aArchitecturezItalyzRavenna. 0aBaptismxHistoryxEarly church, ca. 30-600. 0aBaptismxHistoryyEarly church, ca. 30-600. 0aLight in architecture. 0aLightxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aLiturgies, Early Christian. 0aLiturgy and architecture. 0aWorshipxHistoryxEarly church, ca. 30-600. 0aWorshipxHistoryyEarly church, ca. 30-600. 4aKirchenarchitektur. 4aLiturgie. 4aMittelalter. 4aReformchristentum. 4aTheophany, Light, Baptism, Liturgy. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104181870 cprintz978311037632640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311041808840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110418088423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110418088.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016